	"metadata": {
		"title": "libsoup: infinite loop while reading websocket data (moderate)",
		"reference": [
			{
				"ref_id": "CVE-2024-52532",
				"ref_url": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2024-52532",
				"source": "CVE"
			}
		],
		"description": "DOCUMENTATION: A flaw was found in Libsoup. The soup_websocket_connection_read function uses a loop that reads incoming WebSocket data via the glib library. This issue makes it possible to cause the loop to run indefinitely by sending a continuous stream of data to it. The effect will prevent the DCV service from accepting any further connections, leading to a denial of service.",
